  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\nWith this feature, we'd like to enable generic backend functionality of EdgeFS so that it can be provisioned on top of any Key-Value backend device or existing database. Samsung KVSSDs pioneering approach of moving Key-Value processing inside the NVMe device itself and thus reducing overall CPU utilization associated with heavy I/O.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenMPDK/KVSSD\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nAbility to configure \"rtkvs\" type EdgeFS backends.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\nEdge/IoT Computing endpoints with a requirement for low CPU utilization and high I/O driven by computational AI/ML needs.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n<!-- Specific environment information that helps with the feature request -->\r\n",
